Tarsi short and relatively slender. Protarsomere I short, subtriangular, 1.33 times as long as broad, 0.58 times as long as two following tarsomeres combined, protarsomere II subtriangular, almost as wide as long, protarsomere III very deeply incised (
Fig. 6
).

Male genitalia. Aedeagus (
Fig. 2
) slender, flat, with distinctly prolonged apex.

Female.
Frons broader, pronotum slightly broader and elytra slightly longer than in males (see Variability). Tarsi slightly narrower than in males.Abdomen robust, convex, last ventrite with small round impression in middle. Spermatheca C-shaped with relatively sharp inner angle, spermathecal duct very long with numerous coils (
Fig. 8
). Rectal sclerites (
Figs. 9, 10
): dorsally 3 sclerites (two lateral, 1 central), ventrally 2 wing-shaped sclerites.
